This year's theme is: “Live the Legacy: Towards a socio-economically empowered youth”. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has called for the wavering of experience as a job requirement for young graduates. The president has been addressing crowds gathered at the Orlando Stadium for the commemoration of Youth Day. He criticised the state of youth unemployment in the country. This year's theme is: “Live the Legacy: Towards a socio-economically empowered youth”. WATCH LIVE: Ramaphosa addresses Youth Day commemoration 